#. type: Title #
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Upgrading from Version 2.0"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"> If you haven't used Yii 2.0, you can skip this section and get directly to \"[getting started](../start/prerequisites.md)\"\n"
"> section.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Yii3 keeps many Yii ideas, but it is not a drop-in replacement for Yii 2.0. "
"It uses PHP 8 features, PSR interfaces, dependency injection, explicit "
"package composition, and a different application template. Use your Yii 2.0 "
"experience to design a new Yii3 application deliberately instead of trying "
"to reproduce the old application structure."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "For source applications, compare against:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "[yiisoft/yii2-app-basic](https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2-app-basic)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"[yiisoft/yii2-app-advanced](https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2-app-advanced)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "For the target structure, compare against:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "[yiisoft/app](https://github.com/yiisoft/app)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "[Yii3 guide](../index.md)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Before starting, [check maintenance policy and end-of-life dates for Yii 2.0]"
"(https://www.yiiframework.com/release-cycle).  Keeping a mature Yii 2.0 "
"application on Yii 2.0 can be a valid choice. A Yii3 project is most useful "
"when you want the new package ecosystem, stricter typing, PSR middleware, "
"and a more explicit architecture."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Think of the work as building a Yii3 application that is informed by the old "
"one. The old project tells you which routes, forms, database tables, "
"business rules, and user workflows matter. The Yii3 project should decide "
"again where these responsibilities belong."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Build it in vertical slices:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Create a new Yii3 application with `yiisoft/app`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Configure Composer autoloading and add only the code needed for the slice "
"you are building."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Define configuration and routes before writing actions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Build one request flow at a time: route, action, input model, service, "
"persistence, view, assets, tests."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '5. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Keep the Yii 2.0 application running until each flow is verified in Yii3."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Avoid moving the whole directory tree first. Yii3's defaults are "
"intentionally different, and a mechanical copy tends to preserve Yii 2.0 "
"service-locator assumptions. Prefer small, reviewed decisions over carrying "
"old structure forward because it is familiar."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Prepare the Yii 2.0 application"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Useful preparation can happen before the Yii3 application is ready. These "
"refactorings improve the Yii 2.0 project itself and make the later rewrite "
"less dependent on hidden framework state:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Replace `Yii::$app` access in reusable code with constructor arguments where "
"practical. If a full dependency injection refactoring is too large, keep "
"`Yii::$app` calls near controllers and widgets, then pass values and "
"services to lower-level code explicitly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Introduce repositories or query services for database reads that are "
"currently scattered across controllers, views, widgets, and Active Record "
"methods. Yii3 does not require Active Record for persistence, so a "
"repository boundary gives you a natural place to change the implementation "
"later."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Separate business rules from framework infrastructure. Domain code that does "
"not extend Yii classes, read global application state, or render views is "
"much easier to reuse or rewrite."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Move reusable behavior into Yii 2.0 components or services instead of "
"keeping it inside large controllers and Active Record classes. Yii3 services "
"are configured and injected differently, but the responsibility boundary is "
"similar."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Add tests around routes and workflows you plan to rebuild first. They become "
"the executable specification for the Yii3 slice."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"final class PostRepository\n"
"{\n"
"    public function getArchive(): array\n"
"    {\n"
"        // ...\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    public function getTopForFrontPage(int $limit = 10): array\n"
"    {\n"
"        // ...\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"The Yii3 implementation may still use Active Record, or it may use `yiisoft/"
"db` queries. The important point is that controllers and views no longer "
"need to know that detail."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Some Yii3 application-template choices are worth learning before you start "
"moving features:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"[Application structure](../structure/overview.md). Yii3's default structure "
"is different from Yii 2.0. The structure is flexible, but start with the "
"Yii3 template and change it only when the application needs it."
msgstr ""

