"language.oop5.decon.php#language.oop5.decon.constructor.promotion)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "[Attributes](https://www.php.net/manual/en/language.attributes.php)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Run static analysis and tests on Yii 2.0 before reusing code in Yii3. Code "
"with explicit types, small services, and few implicit `Yii::$app` "
"dependencies is easier to understand and easier to place in the new "
"application."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Yii 2.0 applications commonly keep framework roles in top-level directories:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (text)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"assets/\n"
"commands/\n"
"config/\n"
"controllers/\n"
"models/\n"
"runtime/\n"
"views/\n"
"web/\n"
"widgets/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "The Yii 2.0 advanced template splits the same roles by application:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (text)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"backend/\n"
"common/\n"
"console/\n"
"frontend/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"The current Yii3 application template is organized around source code, "
"configuration, public files, and runtime files:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Yii 2.0 basic | Yii 2.0 advanced | Yii3 |\n"
"|---------------|------------------|------|\n"
"| `controllers/` | `frontend/controllers/`, `backend/controllers/` | `src/Web/*/Action.php` or controller-like classes |\n"
"| `models/` | `common/models/`, app-specific models | `src/Domain`, `src/Shared`, `src/Web/*`, or `src/Db` by responsibility |\n"
"| `views/` | `frontend/views/`, `backend/views/` | templates near the feature, for example `src/Web/HomePage/template.php` |\n"
"| `views/layouts/` | app layout directories | layout classes/templates, for example `src/Web/Shared/Layout/Main` |\n"
"| `assets/` | app asset bundles | `assets/` for source files and `src/Web/.../*Asset.php` for bundles |\n"
"| `web/` | `frontend/web/`, `backend/web/` | `public/` |\n"
"| `commands/` | `console/controllers/` | `src/Console/*Command.php` |\n"
"| `config/*.php` | app and common config files | `config/common`, `config/web`, `config/console`, `config/environments` |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"There is no single required layout. The important change is that Yii3 "
"applications should group code by responsibility and make dependencies "
"explicit. If you are coming from the advanced template, treat `frontend` and "
"`backend` as separate web contexts. Shared domain code can live in `src/"
"Shared` or in application-specific packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Composer and autoloading"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Yii 2.0 applications usually require `vendor/autoload.php` and `vendor/"
"yiisoft/yii2/Yii.php` in `web/index.php`.  Yii3 applications require only "
"Composer's autoloader and application bootstrap code."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Then rebuild Composer autoload files:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Install Yii3 packages intentionally. Yii3 is split into focused packages, so "
"features such as database access, forms, validation, assets, data widgets, "
"authentication, and caching are separate Composer dependencies."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuration and services"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"In Yii 2.0, many services are configured as application components and "
"accessed through the service locator:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$cache = Yii::$app->cache;\n"
"$db = Yii::$app->db;\n"
"$url = Yii::$app->urlManager->createUrl(['post/view', 'id' => $id]);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"In Yii3, services are configured for the container and injected where they "
"are needed:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Psr\\SimpleCache\\CacheInterface;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Db\\Connection\\ConnectionInterface;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Router\\UrlGeneratorInterface;\n"
"\n"
"final readonly class PostService\n"
"{\n"
"    public function __construct(\n"
"        private ConnectionInterface $db,\n"
"        private CacheInterface $cache,\n"
"        private UrlGeneratorInterface $urlGenerator,\n"
"    ) {\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Move configuration in groups:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "aliases to `config/common/aliases.php`;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "route definitions to `config/common/routes.php`;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "shared service definitions to `config/common/di/*.php`;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "web-only service definitions to `config/web/di/*.php`;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "console parameters and commands to `config/console/*.php`;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "shared parameters to `config/common/params.php`;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "environment overrides to `config/environments`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"The default template's `di-console` group reuses shared definitions from "
"`config/common/di/*.php`. If you need console-only container definitions, "
"add the corresponding files to the `di-console` group in `config/"
"configuration.php` and rebuild the merge plan."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Entry script and bootstrap"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "A Yii 2.0 basic entry script commonly creates the application directly:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"defined('YII_DEBUG') or define('YII_DEBUG', true);\n"
"defined('YII_ENV') or define('YII_ENV', 'dev');\n"
"\n"
"require __DIR__ . '/../vendor/autoload.php';\n"
"require __DIR__ . '/../vendor/yiisoft/yii2/Yii.php';\n"
"\n"
"$config = require __DIR__ . '/../config/web.php';\n"
"\n"
"(new yii\\web\\Application($config))->run();\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"In Yii3, use the application template entry script as the source of truth. "
"It loads Composer and bootstraps the configured application runner. Avoid "
"recreating the old `yii\\web\\Application` pattern in `public/index.php`; "
"put configuration in config files and dependencies in the container."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Controllers, actions, and routing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Yii 2.0 routes usually point to controller action methods:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"namespace app\\controllers;\n"
"\n"
"use yii\\web\\Controller;\n"
"\n"
"final class SiteController extends Controller\n"
"{\n"
"    public function actionIndex(): string\n"
"    {\n"
"        return $this->render('index');\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Yii3 does not require controller base classes. The current application "
"template uses invokable action classes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"namespace App\\Web\\HomePage;\n"
"\n"
"use Psr\\Http\\Message\\ResponseInterface;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Yii\\View\\Renderer\\WebViewRenderer;\n"
"\n"
"final readonly class Action\n"
"{\n"
"    public function __construct(\n"
"        private WebViewRenderer $viewRenderer,\n"
"    ) {\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    public function __invoke(): ResponseInterface\n"
"    {\n"
"        return $this->viewRenderer->render(__DIR__ . '/template');\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Routes are explicit:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"When redesigning a controller flow, list all Yii 2.0 actions and create "
"named routes for the flows you still need.  Then implement each flow as an "
"invokable class or a controller-like service. Constructor injection replaces "
"calls to `Yii::$app` and controller properties."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Requests, responses, sessions, and cookies"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Yii 2.0 actions often read request data and write response data through "
"application components:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$id = Yii::$app->request->get('id');\n"
"Yii::$app->session->setFlash('success', 'Saved.');\n"
"\n"
"return $this->redirect(['post/view', 'id' => $id]);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Yii3 uses PSR-7 request and response objects and injectable services:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Psr\\Http\\Message\\ResponseInterface;\n"
"use Psr\\Http\\Message\\ResponseFactoryInterface;\n"
"use Psr\\Http\\Message\\ServerRequestInterface;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Http\\Status;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Router\\UrlGeneratorInterface;\n"
"\n"
"final readonly class SavePostAction\n"
"{\n"
"    public function __construct(\n"
"        private ResponseFactoryInterface $responseFactory,\n"
"        private UrlGeneratorInterface $urlGenerator,\n"
"    ) {\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    public function __invoke(ServerRequestInterface $request): ResponseInterface\n"
"    {\n"
"        $id = (int) ($request->getQueryParams()['id'] ?? 0);\n"
"        $url = $this->urlGenerator->generate('post/view', ['id' => $id]);\n"
"\n"
"        return $this->responseFactory\n"
"            ->createResponse(Status::SEE_OTHER)\n"
"            ->withHeader('Location', $url);\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Design request handling early because it affects forms, filters, REST "
"endpoints, redirects, and tests."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Views, layouts, assets, and URLs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"In Yii 2.0, controller rendering finds files under `views/{controller}` and "
"layouts under `views/layouts`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"return $this->render('view', [\n"
"    'model' => $model,\n"
"]);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "In Yii3, the template path is explicit in the action:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"return $this->viewRenderer->render(__DIR__ . '/view', [\n"
"    'post' => $post,\n"
"]);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"A Yii3 template receives a `Yiisoft\\View\\WebView` instance as `$this`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use App\\Shared\\ApplicationParams;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Html\\Html;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\View\\WebView;\n"
"\n"
"/**\n"
" * @var WebView $this\n"
" * @var ApplicationParams $applicationParams\n"
" * @var string $title\n"
" */\n"
"\n"
"$this->setTitle($title . ' - ' . $applicationParams->name);\n"
"?>\n"
"\n"
"<h1><?= Html::encode($title) ?></h1>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Asset bundles move from `yii\\web\\AssetBundle` to "
"`Yiisoft\\Assets\\AssetBundle`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"namespace App\\Web\\Shared\\Layout\\Main;\n"
"\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Assets\\AssetBundle;\n"
"\n"
"final class MainAsset extends AssetBundle\n"
"{\n"
"    public ?string $basePath = '@assets/main';\n"
"    public ?string $baseUrl = '@assetsUrl/main';\n"
"    public ?string $sourcePath = '@assetsSource/main';\n"
"\n"
"    public array $css = [\n"
"        'site.css',\n"
"    ];\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Register assets in a layout or view via the asset manager:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$assetManager->register(MainAsset::class);\n"
"\n"
"$this->addCssFiles($assetManager->getCssFiles());\n"
"$this->addJsFiles($assetManager->getJsFiles());\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Replace `yii\\helpers\\Url` and `Yii::$app->urlManager` usage with named routes and\n"
"`Yiisoft\\Router\\UrlGeneratorInterface`:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "$url = $urlGenerator->generate('post/view', ['id' => $post->getId()]);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"See [View](../views/view.md), [Assets](../views/asset.md), [Scripts, styles "
"and metatags](../views/script-style-meta.md), and [Template engines](../"
"views/template-engines.md)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Forms and validation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Yii 2.0 frequently combines form data, labels, validation, and sometimes "
"persistence in a `yii\\base\\Model` or `yii\\db\\ActiveRecord` class:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"final class ContactForm extends \\yii\\base\\Model\n"
"{\n"
"    public $name;\n"
"    public $email;\n"
"\n"
"    public function rules(): array\n"
"    {\n"
"        return [\n"
"            [['name', 'email'], 'required'],\n"
"            ['email', 'email'],\n"
"        ];\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Yii3 separates these concerns. Use `yiisoft/form-model` for form data and "
"metadata, and `yiisoft/validator` for rules:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"For form rendering, replace `yii\\widgets\\ActiveForm` with `yiisoft/form` "
"fields and form model integration. For input hydration, prefer the form-"
"model and hydrator packages instead of mass-assigning arbitrary request data "
"to persistence objects."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Active Record and persistence"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"There are two common Yii3 choices for code that used Yii 2.0 Active Record "
"classes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"The first path is architectural: move business logic to services and domain "
"objects, then use repositories for persistence. This is recommended when the "
"Yii 2.0 model contains validation, form scenarios, authorization checks, "
"mailing, file uploads, and database access in the same class."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"The second path is incremental: represent the database model with [yiisoft/"
"active-record](https://github.com/yiisoft/active-record). This is closer to "
"Yii 2.0 and can be significantly faster when your Active Record classes "
"mostly describe tables and relations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Yii 2.0:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"final class Post extends \\yii\\db\\ActiveRecord\n"
"{\n"
"    public static function tableName(): string\n"
"    {\n"
"        return '{{%post}}';\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    public function rules(): array\n"
"    {\n"
"        return [\n"
"            [['title', 'body'], 'required'],\n"
"            ['title', 'string', 'max' => 255],\n"
"        ];\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Yii3 Active Record:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\ActiveRecord\\ActiveRecord;\n"
"\n"
"final class Post extends ActiveRecord\n"
"{\n"
"    protected int $id;\n"
"    protected string $title;\n"
"    protected string $body;\n"
"\n"
"    public function tableName(): string\n"
"    {\n"
"        return '{{%post}}';\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    public function getId(): ?int\n"
"    {\n"
"        return $this->id ?? null;\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    public function getTitle(): ?string\n"
"    {\n"
"        return $this->title ?? null;\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    public function setTitle(string $title): void\n"
"    {\n"
"        $this->title = $title;\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Do not move Yii 2.0 `rules()` directly into the Active Record class. In "
"Yii3, validation belongs to validator rules, form models, command objects, "
"or services:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\FormModel\\FormModel;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Length;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Required;\n"
"\n"
"final class PostInput extends FormModel\n"
"{\n"
"    #[Required]\n"
"    #[Length(max: 255)]\n"
"    public ?string $title = null;\n"
"\n"
"    #[Required]\n"
"    public ?string $body = null;\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Then copy validated data into the record or pass it to an application "
"service:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$post = new Post();\n"
"$post->setTitle($input->title);\n"
"$post->save();\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "When deciding what to reuse, check each Active Record method:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"table mapping and relations can usually move to `yiisoft/active-record`;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "validation should move to `yiisoft/validator`;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "form labels and hints should move to `yiisoft/form-model`;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "search models should become query/data-reader services;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "business workflows should become services;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "events should use PSR-14 events or package-specific events;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"direct `Yii::$app->db` usage should become injected database dependencies."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Yii 2.0 migrations and Yii3 `yiisoft/db-migration` migrations are not "
"compatible. Start a new migration history or create structure dumps for the "
"current schema, then use Yii3 migrations for future schema changes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Yii 2.0 `GridView` is commonly used with `ActiveDataProvider`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use yii\\grid\\GridView;\n"
"\n"
"echo GridView::widget([\n"
"    'dataProvider' => $dataProvider,\n"
"    'filterModel' => $searchModel,\n"
"    'columns' => [\n"
"        'id',\n"
"        'title',\n"
"        'created_at:datetime',\n"
"        ['class' => 'yii\\grid\\ActionColumn'],\n"
"    ],\n"
"]);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Yii3 uses [yiisoft/yii-dataview](https://github.com/yiisoft/yii-dataview). "
"It renders data from a data reader and uses fluent widget configuration:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\Data\\Reader\\ReadableDataInterface;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Yii\\DataView\\Column\\DataColumn;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Yii\\DataView\\GridView\\Column\\ActionColumn;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Yii\\DataView\\GridView\\GridView;\n"
"\n"
"/**\n"
" * @var ReadableDataInterface $dataReader\n"
" */\n"
"\n"
"echo GridView::widget()\n"
"    ->dataReader($dataReader)\n"
"    ->columns(\n"
"        new DataColumn('id'),\n"
"        new DataColumn('title', header: 'Title'),\n"
"        new DataColumn('created_at', header: 'Created'),\n"
"        new ActionColumn(),\n"
"    );\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"For sorting, pagination, filtering, and action URLs, wire the widget to Yii "
"Router:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\Yii\\DataView\\YiiRouter\\ActionColumnUrlConfig;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Yii\\DataView\\YiiRouter\\ActionColumnUrlCreator;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Yii\\DataView\\YiiRouter\\UrlCreator;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Yii\\DataView\\YiiRouter\\UrlParameterProvider;\n"
"\n"
"echo GridView::widget()\n"
"    ->dataReader($dataReader)\n"
"    ->urlParameterProvider(new UrlParameterProvider($currentRoute))\n"
"    ->urlCreator(new UrlCreator($urlGenerator))\n"
"    ->columns(\n"
"        new DataColumn('id'),\n"
"        new DataColumn('title'),\n"
"        new ActionColumn(\n"
"            urlCreator: new ActionColumnUrlCreator($urlGenerator, $currentRoute),\n"
"            urlConfig: new ActionColumnUrlConfig(baseRouteName: 'post'),\n"
"        ),\n"
"    );\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "A Yii 2.0 search model usually becomes a query service that:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "reads filter and sort parameters from the request;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "validates them with `yiisoft/validator`;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "builds a database query or repository query;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "exposes a data reader to GridView."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"See [Using htmx for partial reloads](../../cookbook/using-htmx-for-partial-"
"reloads.md) for a complete Yii3 GridView workflow and [yii-dataview GridView "
"docs](https://github.com/yiisoft/yii-dataview/blob/master/docs/en/guide/"
"gridview.md)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Filters, middleware, and access control"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Yii 2.0 controller filters and behaviors usually look like this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"public function behaviors(): array\n"
"{\n"
"    return [\n"
"        'access' => [\n"
"            'class' => \\yii\\filters\\AccessControl::class,\n"
"            'rules' => [\n"
"                ['allow' => true, 'roles' => ['@']],\n"
"            ],\n"
"        ],\n"
"    ];\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"In Yii3, request processing is middleware-based. Move cross-cutting concerns "
"such as authentication, authorization, body parsing, locale negotiation, "
"CSRF checks, and error handling to middleware or dedicated services. Keep "
"actions focused on the request flow they implement."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Console commands"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Yii 2.0 console commands extend `yii\\console\\Controller`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"final class ReportController extends \\yii\\console\\Controller\n"
"{\n"
"    public function actionSend(): int\n"
"    {\n"
"        // ...\n"
"        return self::EXIT_CODE_NORMAL;\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Yii3 console commands are services in `src/Console`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"namespace App\\Console;\n"
"\n"
"use Symfony\\Component\\Console\\Attribute\\AsCommand;\n"
"use Symfony\\Component\\Console\\Command\\Command;\n"
"use Symfony\\Component\\Console\\Input\\InputInterface;\n"
"use Symfony\\Component\\Console\\Output\\OutputInterface;\n"
"\n"
"#[AsCommand(name: 'report/send')]\n"
"final class SendReportCommand extends Command\n"
"{\n"
"    protected function execute(InputInterface $input, OutputInterface $output): int\n"
"    {\n"
"        // ...\n"
"        return Command::SUCCESS;\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Move command dependencies to constructor injection and register commands in "
"console configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Yii 2.0 REST controllers, serializers, and response formatters do not move "
"directly to Yii3. Start from PSR-7 responses and explicit routing. Build one "
"resource at a time:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "define routes for collection and item operations;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"inject request, persistence, serializer, and response factory dependencies;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "validate input with `yiisoft/validator`;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "return JSON responses through Yii3 response helpers or PSR-7 factories;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '5. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "move authentication and rate limiting to middleware."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"See [Response](../runtime/response.md), [Authentication](../security/"
"authentication.md), and [Authorization](../security/authorization.md)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Do not postpone tests until the whole Yii3 application is done. For each new "
"request flow, add:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "unit tests for services and validators;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "functional tests for actions and middleware;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "end-to-end tests for critical browser flows;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "static analysis for stricter type checks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"Yii3 code is more explicit, so tests should assert services directly instead "
"of constructing large application component arrays."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid ""
"See [Testing overview](../testing/overview.md), [Unit tests](../testing/"
"unit.md), [Functional tests](../testing/functional.md), and [End-to-end "
"tests](../testing/end-to-end.md)."
